main event: A silver, circular, saucer-shaped object was observed over Danville, California on 2-5-52 at 2030 PST by a private citizen for 30 seconds. The object maneuvered rapidly and was estimated to be faster than a jet aircraft.
interesting points: The object was described as silver, circular, and saucer-shaped, displaying erratic behavior and moving faster than a jet aircraft.
The observation lasted for 30 seconds, providing a significant duration of the sighting.
The witness reported the object, and a questionnaire was filled out to document the details of the sighting.
The witness was a high school student at the time of the observation, adding credibility to the report.
A weather data sheet was included to note atmospheric conditions during the sighting.
